SIMPLE: midland
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Midland
<hw>Mid"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Being in
the interior country; distant from the coast or seashore; <as>as,
<ex>midland</ex> towns or inhabitants</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Surrounded by the land; mediterranean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And on the <qex>midland</qex> sea the French had awed.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Midland</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Midland
<hw>Mid"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The interior or
central region of a country; -- usually in the plural.</def>
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Midmain</ent>⟦br⟧
